CNCP v1 23315
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#9277: DefineProps don't convert generic type to Object",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:36.233278+00:00",
  "text": "DefineProps don't convert generic type to Object\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.4\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://play.vuejs.org/#\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. create a generic component\r\n2. define props with the generic type: `Object as PropType<T>`\r\n3. define a function which has props in parameters\r\n4. execute the function with defined props\r\n5. catch the following error\r\n![image](https://github.com/vuejs/core/assets/32462262/798c57b0-f0dc-489d-9a74-a69d11a3f65a)\r\n\n\n### What is expected?\n\nprop modelValue has a `T` type\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nat the line `useTestUseCase(props);` has error\r\n![image](https://github.com/vuejs/core/assets/32462262/b505e5e6-7eb2-4532-a70c-de0a14896983)\r\n\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types",
    ":cake: p2-nice-to-have"
  ],
